                <h1>Understanding Japanese Feudalism: Structure & Impact</h1>
                <p>Japanese feudalism was a complex social structure that dominated Japan from the 12th to the 19th century. It was characterized by the relationship between lords (daimyō), vassals (samurai), and peasants. Land was exchanged for loyalty and military service, creating a hierarchical society where loyalty and honor held paramount importance.</p>
